E = {natural numbers, prime numbers, finite sets, contradiction}; Ro = {primes: elements under
study, finite set: assumed bound, contradiction: proof mechanism}; I = {logical consistency,
arithmetic validity, law of excluded middle}
Initial Tension Tensor T_0:
Q = {Is the set of primes infinite?}; Co = {assumption of finitude vs. constructive generation of
new prime}; G = {prove or disprove infinitude}; U = {high — answer unknown}
Resolution Trajectory R:
b1: Assume finite set P = {p1, p2, ..., pn}. delta_T: introduces contradiction target, tension shifts to
productive. b2: Construct N = (p1 * p2 * ... * pn) + 1. delta_T: creates new object not divisible by
any element of P. b3: N is either prime or has a prime factor not in P. delta_T: -1 (closes conflict).
b4: Either way, P was not complete. Contradiction. delta_T: -|Co| (conflict resolved). Closure: |T_n|
= 0. Q resolved, Co empty, G achieved, U = 0.
